Additionally, the paper mentions explicitly stated models of agents' decision-making, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the beliefs of agents and opponents, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of agents, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
